### File Structure
```
NewsPortal/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── article_catalog.html
│   ├── article_details.html
│   ├── bookmarks.html
│   ├── comments.html
│   ├── write_comment.html
│   ├── trending.html
│   ├── category.html
│   └── search_results.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (optional thumbnails or icons)
│
└── data/
    ├── articles.txt
    ├── categories.txt
    ├── bookmarks.txt
    ├── comments.txt
    └── trending.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file implementing the web server, routing, and all business logic. It handles reading and writing to the local text files in the 'data' directory, processes user requests, and renders the appropriate HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here.

- templates/
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the nine pages defined in the requirements. Each HTML file corresponds to one page and includes the specified elements with their IDs for frontend rendering and interaction.

  - dashboard.html: Template for the Dashboard Page.
  - article_catalog.html: Template for the Article Catalog Page.
  - article_details.html: Template for the Article Details Page.
  - bookmarks.html: Template for the Bookmarks Page.
  - comments.html: Template for the Comments Page.
  - write_comment.html: Template for the Write Comment Page.
  - trending.html: Template for the Trending Articles Page.
  - category.html: Template for the Category Page.
  - search_results.html: Template for the Search Results Page.

- static/
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images used by the frontend.

  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across all pages.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity, such as button actions and dynamic content updates.
  - images/: Optional folder for article thumbnails or UI icons.

- data/
  Stores all application data in local text files as specified.

  - articles.txt: Stores all news articles.
  - categories.txt: Stores news categories.
  - bookmarks.txt: Stores user bookmarks.
  - comments.txt: Stores comments on articles.
  - trending.txt: Stores trending articles data.
```
